through his energy and finances, lyman dayton was instrumental in bringing the railroad into  and development of the lake superior and mississippi railroad, of which he was president until 1865. according to the united states census bureau, the city has a total area of 25.2 square miles (65.2 km2), of which, 23.5 square miles (60.7 km2) of it is land and 1.7 square miles (4.5 km2) of it (6.83%) is water.